cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with hand keypoint detection in single images using a multi-camera system. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions 3D markerless hand motion capture, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper describes a procedure for improving the accuracy of a keypoint detector through iterative training using labeled data. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper deals with 3D triangulation and reprojection of keypoints. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with processing and analyzing images from multiple cameras.
